-- Italy Plans to Postpone Vat Hike by 2% to July 2013, Ansa Says
-- B y   C h i a r a   V a s a r r i
-- 2012-07-05T14:23:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-05/italy-plans-to-postpone-vat-hike-by-2-to-july-2013-ansa-says.html
     July 5 (Bloomberg) --Prime Minister  Mario Monti ’s
government may postpone a 2 percentage points increase of the
value-added tax planned for October to July 2013, news agency
Ansa reported, citing a draft of a decree law that is being
discussed at a cabinet meeting today.  The draft doesn’t include any plan, previously reported by
the Italian press, to freeze the rates for electricity, gas,
water and transportation until 2013, Ansa said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chiara Vasarri in Rome at 
